\section{Statistical Method}{

The Linear Combination Test tests the null hypothesis: "No linear combination
of genes in a set is associated with the phenotype." It uses:
\enumerate{
\item Covariance matrix estimation with regularization
\item Eigenvalue decomposition for orthogonal transformation
\item T²-like test statistic on transformed data
\item Permutation-based p-value calculation
\item FDR correction for multiple gene sets
}
}

\section{Method Selection}{

